    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-04-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="545"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Reid</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-04-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 582.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to Mr. Carter’s No. 567 of the
                    31st ultimo, relating to the annexation of the Kongo by Belgium, which inclosed
                    a copy of a dispatch on that subject from Sir Edward Grey to the British
                    minister at Brussels, in which reference was made to a memorandum which should
                    have accompanied the dispatch, I now have <pb facs="0670" n="568"
                        xml:id="pg_568"/> the honor to inclose<note n="1" xml:id="d545fn1">See
                        Africa No. 3, printed in S. Doc. No. 147, 61st Cong., 1st sess., entitled
                        “Affairs in the Kongo.”</note> herewith a copy of the memorandum in
                    question, which I have received to-day from the foreign office.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitelaw Reid.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
